http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/telangana/Leader-remembered/article13980009.ece

The Communist Party of India Karimnagar district unit leaders condoled the death of veteran communist leader A.B. Bardhan in Karimnagar town on Sunday.At a condolence meeting at the party office, CPI district secretary K. Ramgopal Reddy, town secretary P. Raju, and district leaders B. Ashok, B. Sadashiva, among others, garlanded his portrait and paid floral tributes. On this occasion, they recollected the visit of Bardhan to Karimnagar town in 2012 to participate in State CPI convention and his fight demanding statehood for Telangana.